  (text "POWER ARCHITECTURE NOTES (IPC-2221B / IPC-2152):\n\nVIN RAIL (7-24V):\n  Dual entry: J_VIN_JACK (barrel, primary) + J_VIN_TERM (screw, alternate)\n  C_P1 100µF 35V bulk close to connector for inrush handling\n  PCB trace: 1.5mm min (IPC-2152: 3A, 1oz Cu, 10°C rise, outer layer)\n  Polygon pour on F.Cu and B.Cu preferred, stitched every 3mm\n\nBUCK CONVERTER TPS54331 (VIN→+5V/3A):\n  Switching frequency: 570kHz (R_P2=100kΩ on RT pin)\n  Output voltage: 5.00V (R_P3=1.0MΩ, R_P4=196kΩ VSENSE divider)\n  Catch diode D_P1 (SS34): place anode to GND, cathode to PH within 5mm of U7\n  Inductor L_P1 (10µH/3A): place close to PH pin, between D_P1 and output caps\n  PH node (switching): minimize copper area to reduce EMI\n  PGND star: separate from signal GND, single via connection to GND plane\n  C_P6 (COMP): 10kΩ + 100nF Type II compensation — adjust during bring-up\n  C_P7 (SS): 100nF → ~5ms soft-start ramp\n  EN pin: tie to VIN (always-on) via 100kΩ pullup — modify for power sequencing\n\nLDO AMS1117-3.3 (+5V→+3V3):\n  Tab pin (pin 2) = output: thermal via array under tab, 4 vias min\n  C_P8 (10µF input) + C_P9 (10µF output) within 2mm of AMS1117\n  AMS1117 requires ≥10µF ESR ≥20mΩ on output for stability\n  Use X5R 0805 (ESR ~5mΩ at 100Hz) — add series 22mΩ trace if needed\n\nHUB75 PANEL POWER:\n  J_HUB_JACK + J_HUB_TERM: isolated from carrier VIN path\n  C_P11 (1000µF): handles LED switching inrush on large panels\n  Route +5V_HUB75 directly to HUB75 IDC pins — do not share with logic\n  Heavy polygon pour: 3mm+ width, both layers, via stitched\n\nAVDD FERRITE (FB1): +3V3→AVDD for ES8388 analog supply\n  Defined here; AVDD net distributed to audio_codec sheet"
    (at 20 130 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
